original: Ågren, Erik Gustaf, ingenjör, direktör, Göteborg, f. ,24/6/9’3 i Gbg av grossh. Axel H. Å. o. Louise Schmidt. G. 22 m. Jane Lisbeth Detthow. Barn: Berit f. 23’ g. m. dr Gunnar Hammer, Sthlm. — Stud :ex. v. Gbgs h. real 12, stud. v. KTH o. HHS, res:off:ex. 17, praktik i Engl., Tyskl. o. Frankr. 20- 22. Medarb. i grossh :firman Axel H. Ågren i Gbg fr. 22, deläg. sed. dess omibild. t. Axel H. Ågren A-B 32 o. chef f. kemikalieavd. Styr :led. i Gbgs Sand A-B, Kemikaliehand. imp ifören. i Sthlm, led. av Sv. grossistförb. branschnd f. droger, färger o. kemikalier. Hobbies: konst, filateli, trädgårdsarkitektur.
translated: Ågren, Erik Gustaf, engineer, director, Gothenburg, b. 24/6/93 in Gothenburg, son of wholesaler Axel H. Å. and Louise Schmidt. Married 22 with Jane Lisbeth Detthow. Children: Berit b. 23, married to Dr. Gunnar Hammer, Stockholm. Education: graduated from Gothenburg high school 12, studied at KTH and HHS, officer candidate exam 17, internships in England, Germany, and France 20-22. Employee at wholesale company Axel H. Ågren in Gothenburg from 22, co-owner since its reestablishment as Axel H. Ågren A-B 32, and head of the chemical department. Board member of Gothenburg Sand A-B, Importers of Chemicals trade association in Stockholm, member of the Swedish Wholesalers Association branch for drugs, paints, and chemicals. Hobbies: art, philately, garden architecture.
